results.name: Number of non-isomorphic multiset partitions of weight n with at least one endpoint.
comment: The weight of a multiset partition is the sum of sizes of its parts. Weight is generally not the same as number of vertices.
An endpoint is a vertex appearing only once (degree 1).
Also the number of non-isomorphic multiset partitions of weight n with at least one singleton.
example: Non-isomorphic representatives of the a(1) = 1 through a(4) = 21 multiset partitions:
xref: The case of set-systems is A330053 (singletons) or A330052 (endpoints).
The complement is counted by A302545.
